      "instruction": "1Preheat waffle iron and grease with cooking spray."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "2Combine all of the ingredients, except for the sour cream, in a large mixing bowl; mix and stir until thoroughly incorporated."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "3If you want smaller waffles, scoop out about 1/3 cup of the batter and form into a patty. For bigger waffles, use 1/2 cup of the batter. For a perfect serving size, use 2 ounces of the batter per waffle."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "4Transfer to preheated waffle iron and close; cook for 3 to 4 minutes, or until cooked through and browned on top. Cooking time will depend on the size of the waffles."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "5Remove from waffle iron, top with a sprinkle of cheese (optional) and set aside."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "6Repeat with the remaining batter."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "7Serve the potato waffles with sour cream and fresh chives."
